HEADWORD: meadow grass
<hw>meadow grass</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>Any of various grasses that thrive in the presence of abundant
moisture, especially those of the genus <gen>Poa</gen>, common in
meadows, and of great value for hay and for pasture. See
<er>Grass</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

